README.md
     1â†’# color
     3â†’Color lets you use colorized outputs in terms of [ANSI Escape
     4â†’Codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ANSI_escape_code#Colors) in Go (Golang). It
     5â†’has support for Windows too! The API can be used in several ways, pick one that
     6â†’suits you.
     7â†’
     8â†’![Color](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/438920/96832689-03b3e000-13f4-11eb-9803-46f4c4de3406.jpg)
     9â†’
    10â†’## Install
    12â†’```
    13â†’go get github.com/fatih/color
    14â†’```
    15â†’
    16â†’## Examples
    18â†’### Standard colors
    33â†’### RGB colors
    45â†’### Mix and reuse colors
    71â†’### Use your own output (io.Writer)
    81â†’### Custom print functions (PrintFunc)
    94â†’### Custom fprint functions (FprintFunc)
   105â†’### Insert into noncolor strings (SprintFunc)
   124â†’### Plug into existing code
   142â†’### Disable/Enable color
   177â†’## GitHub Actions
   179â†’To output color in GitHub Actions (or other CI systems that support ANSI colors), make sure to set `color.NoColor = false` so that it bypasses the check for non-tty output streams. 
